

'''= historical and reconstituted Kyrgyz [[Land Commons]]'''

=Description=

Antonia Malchik:

"The Kyrgyz Republic once had a successful system of grazing that benefited both herdsmen and the land. Shattered during Soviet times in favour of intensive production, the grazing commons is slowly being reinstated after passage of a Pasture Law in 2009, replacing a system of private leases with public use rights that revolve around ecological knowledge and are determined by local communities."
(https://aeon.co/essays/is-it-time-to-upend-the-idea-that-land-is-private-property?)

